---
title: Spiced Lentil Burger with Zesty Salad
description: Every week, literally thousands of you wonderful cooks give us feedback on our recipes via the little questionnaire we email to you. And every week Ellie reads through every single answer (we’ve given her a comfortable chair and as much tea as necessary, to ease the process). We’ve had a lot of requests from our veggie customers recently for a delicious veggie burger, so André headed into the kitchen to create this masterpiece! Let us know what you think!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/spiced-lentil-burger-wk47-33aa13b9.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/spiced-lentil-burger-wk47-e5a85cf6.pdf
cuisine: American
time required: 45 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/spiced-lentil-burger-wk47-57ecf49d383a7f0d653063c2
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
servings: 2
---

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one!). Cut the @red onion{1}(cut in half through the root, peeled and chopped into ½cm chunks). Roughly chop the @fresh coriander{2%sprigs}. Heat a #frying pan{} on medium heat with a drizzle of oil. Cook your onion for ~{5%minutes}, then add half your garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Drain the @butter beans{1%400g can} in a #colander{} and rinse under cold water. Transfer your beans to a #bowl{} and mash with a #potato masher{} or fork. Add half your coriander, the @red Thai style paste{1%tbsp}, a generous pinch of salt, your onion and mix well. Wipe the frying pan with @kitchen paper{}, as you will use it again later.

Drain the @green lentils{1%400g can}, rinse under cold water and add to your bean mixture. Tip in the @panko breadcrumbs{30%g} along with 2 tbsp of water per person. Mix well and then firmly shape into even-sized burgers with your hands.

> Make sure they are well squidged together. There will be some leftover mix; shape it into smaller patties and you'll have extra falafels!

Pop the burgers in your #fridge{} while you make your yoghurt dressing and salad. Zest and juice the @lime{1}. Mix half your juice and half your zest to the @Greek style natural yoghurt{1%150g tub} along with your remaining garlic. Season with a pinch of salt and then stir in the rest of your coriander.

Cut the root off the @baby gem lettuce{1} and separate the leaves. Slice half of the @vine tomatoes{2} and chop the rest into wedges. Pop your tomato wedges into a bowl with two-thirds of your baby gem leaves.

== Zesty Salad Dressing ==

To make the zesty salad dressing, peel and grate the @ginger{1%small piece}. In a #small bowl{}, mix your ginger with your remaining lime juice and zest. Add a pinch of @?sugar{2%tsp} and stir well, then mix in 1 tbsp of @olive oil{2%tbsp} and season with a pinch of salt.

== Assembly ==

Cut each @brioche bun{2} in half. Heat the frying pan on medium-high heat (no need for oil) and place each bun cut-side down for ~{30%seconds}, until lightly toasted. Add a glug of oil to the pan and when the oil is hot, carefully cook your burgers for ~{5%minutes} on each side or until golden brown.

> Use a #fish slice{} to turn them over as they can be fragile!

Pour your zesty salad dressing over your salad and toss. Smear the insides of each bun with some of your yoghurt dressing and pop two baby gem leaves on each base. Sit your burger on top followed by a couple of slices of tomato. Pop on the top of your bun and serve with a generous pile of your salad and any remaining yoghurt dressing on the side. Enjoy!